Videomass2 Builds and Installation Instructions

Base Dependencies:

    - python 2.7 
    - wxPython 3.0
    - pip

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------#
NOTE: [Linux/Macintosh/Unix/Windows]

Videomass2 can be run without installing by un-tarring the source package and 
executing the "launcher" script in the root of the un-tarred directory.
Alternatively, however, if you want the setup.py script to allow you to build 
an executable for your operating system or if you simply want to install 
Videomass2 from the python Package Index (aka PyPi) follow the Options below.

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------#
Option 1) Installing from Pypi: [Linux/Macintosh/Unix/Windows]

pip install videomass2

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------#
Option 2) Build a Windows exe: [Windows]

please, visit the following support page to Windows paragraph.

https://jeanslack.github.io/Videomass2/building_package.html

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------#
Option 3) Build a MacOSX app: [Macintosh OSX]

please, visit the following support page to MacOsX paragraph.

https://jeanslack.github.io/Videomass2/building_package.html

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------#
Option 4) Build as wheel: [Linux/Macintosh/Unix/Windows]

please, visit the following support page to Build distribution for Windows, 
MacOsX, Linux, Unix paragraph.

https://jeanslack.github.io/Videomass2/building_package.html

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------#
Option 5) Build as Debian package: [Linux/Macintosh/Unix/Windows]

please, visit the following support page to Gnu/Linux Debian paragraph.
    
https://jeanslack.github.io/Videomass2/building_package.html
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------#




